SimpleNBAuthModule
public class SimplePasswordNBAuthModule
extends AbstractSimpleNBAuthModule

Simple password authentication module.

The purpose of this authentication module is to implement a simple plain text password authentication exchange. The server requests a password in an AuthRequest and the client must return the matching password string.

Note: Because there is no encryption, this authentication module is only suitable when using an encrypted channel (e.g., SSL) or when there is some other physical guarantee of privacy for the network connection.

This simple password authentication module has only one optional module initialization parameter: the JsonNode initialization root object may contain the field name "password_field_name" to specify an alternate password field name string used in the element definition nodes. The default is "password".

Simple password authentication module elements must contain a password string. The element definition JsonNode may be a textual node directly representing the password, or it may be an object node containing the named password field. If a JsonNode object is specified, then all object fields other than the password field are converted to NameValPB elements added to the "dict" member of the AuthenRequestPB's authenData field (via the JsonUtil.AddDictEntry(java.lang.String,com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode, org.openflow.northboundapi.proto.ValuesPB.ValuePB.Builder) conversion method), providing any contextual information for the password being requested (e.g., in the case where multiple passwords may be contained in one request).
